[normal]Written evidence submitted by Global Partners Governance[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]About the author[bold]Greg Power[bold] has been involved in political and parliamentary reform for around 20 years. He co-founded Global Partners in 2005 to deliver projects to strengthen representative politics
[normal], since working in countries in the Middle East, sub-Saharan Africa and Latin America
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]He 
[normal]provides direct support to politicians and ministers, developing strategies and helping to manage the process of political 
[normal]and parliamentary reform
[normal].
[normal] 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]He has also provided advice to a variety of international organisations and donor agencies helping, amongst others, the Danish foreign ministry to establish their multi-party institute, and International IDEA to evaluate their work on political parties.
[normal] 
[normal] He writes widely on issues such as the application of political economy analysis, donor approaches to governance assistance, and parliamentary transparency. 
[normal] 
[normal]He is the author of the first 
[normal]Global Parliamentary Report
[normal], published by the UNDP and IPU in 2012.
